**About us:**
**EveryMatrix** 
 is a leading B2B SaaS provider delivering iGaming software, content and services. We provide casino, sports betting, platform and payments, and affiliate management to
 **200 customers worldwide.**
 But that's not all! We're not just about numbers,
 **we're about people** 
 . With a team of over 1000 passionate individuals spread across twelve countries in Europe, Asia, and the US, we're all united by our love for innovation and teamwork.




 Join us on this exciting journey as we continue to redefine the iGaming landscape, one groundbreaking solution at a time.




**We’re looking for a creative and resourceful JavaScript/TypeScript Game Developer
 **to join our team in Stockholm.****
**What you'll get to do:**
* Make amazing games, from wacky ideas all the way to finished products;
* Game development using JavaScript/Typescript + Pixi.JS;
* Maintenance of existing games;
* Contributing to framework.


**What you need to know:**
* 3+ years of prior experience in software development;
* Strong experience with JavaScript/TypeScript;
* Pixi JS experience - must-have;
* Understanding Spine and pixi-spine library;
* Strong knowledge of OOP, SOLID principles and Clean Code principles;
* Experience working in gaming;
* Experience in structured software development;
* Good level of written and spoken English.


**Here's what we offer:**
* Pension Plan: Standard employer contribution of 4.2%, providing a secure foundation for your future financial well-being.
* Long-Term Disability and Injury Insurance: Coverage through Euro Accident, ensuring financial support in case of unexpected events.
* Comprehensive Health Insurance: Access to high-quality healthcare services, tailored to meet your needs.
* Health Care Allowance: Additional financial support for personal health-related expenses.


 At EveryMatrix, we're committed to creating a supportive and inclusive workplace where you can thrive both personally and professionally. Come join us and experience the difference!




 EveryMatrix is a member of the World Lottery Association (WLA) and European Lotteries Association. In September 2023 it became the first iGaming supplier to receive WLA Safer Gambling Certification. EveryMatrix is proud of its commitment to safer gambling and player protection whilst producing market leading gaming solutions.

We’re growing quickly and looking for a driven System Tester who wants to work in our team ensuring the security, quality and performance of our banking platform – Vilja Platform.

Vilja Platform is the cloud solution that gives us the opportunity say "Let's shape the future of banking. Together." and it incorporates our collected experiences from building and delivering premium banking solutions to the market for more than 14 years.

The role of System Tester requires a lot of personal engagement and drive, and an ability to visualize solutions in a wider context. You will listen to customer requirements, understand market trends, follow the technical evolution and keep abreast of the regulatory landscape that governs much of our customers’ businesses. An important part of your work is to communicate with different stakeholders, interpret functional and non-functional requirements as well as act as a bridge between requirement owners and the development teams.



**What you need to succeed:**  

Being able to work on site (Stockholm) 3 days a week;

Strong communication skills;

Fluent in English;

At least 5 years of experience in the software industry working as a software test engineer, software developer or equivalent;

Experience testing complex software systems;

Experience testing web-based systems;

Relational databases, including traditional SQL as well as ORM technologies;

NoSQL database Mongo DB;

QA Certification (ISTQB or similar);

Experience in Test Automation preferably Selenium + Java (but could be any other object-oriented language);



**Nice to have:**  

Bachelor's degree or equivalent in computer science field.

Experience with API testing (Postman, SoapUI);

Knowledge of HTTP protocol;

Experience with Linux;

Experience with Kubernetes;

Previous experience with FinTech related projects or industries;

Evolution is a multinational business at the forefront of the online gaming industry. We have an extensive track record of number 1s and are always looking for great people to help us create the next big product hit. Our team of 1,000+ engineers operates out of 8 engineering hubs running code 24/7/365 to serve users around the world. This is run through a modern software stack that supports over 250 fully automated releases per month in our main live environment. We believe in building in-house competence and agile work processes so that we can deliver on our Engineering mission:
 *A flawless player experience.*
**Job Description**
 We appreciate all applications and interest in Evolution. This is a hybrid - role based in Stockholm, Sweden.




 We’re now looking for a motivated QA talent to join our amazing NetEnt team in Stockholm for a temporary position! As part of Evolution, a leader in one of the world’s fastest-growing industries, you’ll have the chance to help us break new ground and shape the future of gaming.




 Managing and ensuring the quality of a large portfolio of games is a core responsibility of our team. The role requires attention to detail and strong organizational skills to keep track of various game features, updates, and potential issues. Given the temporary nature of the role, it’s well-suited to someone who can quickly get up to speed with existing processes and workflows. With Evolution’s presence in the gaming industry, the position is ideal for you, with experience or interest in casino games.




 Responsibilities:




* Be a proactive member of our development team, collaborating closely with Product Owners, Designers, Developers, and other QA team members.
* Working alongside distributed teams to enhance collaboration and ensure seamless product delivery;
* Performing manual testing to validate features and requirements;
* Planning and executing test cases, writing test plans, and documenting bugs in detail;
* Participating in release process activities;
* Assessing product usability and reliability, providing valuable feedback and recommendations for improvements;
* Be prepared to learn, build your skills and knowledge, and share them with the team.


**Qualifications**
 Qualifications




* 3+ years of professional experience in software and functional testing;
* Understanding of software development processes, stages, concepts and methodologies of Quality Assurance;
* Experience in both web and mobile testing;
* Experience with Postman and version control systems (e.g., Git);
* Understanding of CI/CD pipelines and tools like Jenkins;
* Proficient in English, both written and spoken;
* Strong analytical and diagnostic skills, attention to details;
* Willingness to ask for help from colleagues and to help others.
* Nice-to-have:
* Experience with Kibana;
* Previous experience in casino games or related gaming environments;
* Knowledge of TypeScript basics, CSS, XPath.


**Additional Information**
 Exciting opportunity at our brand new office in the heart of Stockholm with amazing colleagues! Join our dynamic international team and be a part of a vibrant work environment where innovation thrives. Embrace the city´s energy as you contribute to our company´s growth!




 Evolution provides a dynamic and creative work environment with a unique opportunity for the right people to enhance their skills and drive their passion. Our culture is rooted in Evolution’s core values ALIVE, do RIGHT and work TOGETHER and we operate guided by our vision to become the leading supplier of online casino in the world.




**Our Benefits Are**
* Competitive pension, health and medical insurance
* 30 paid vacation days
* Fitness benefit (Friskvårdsbidrag)
* Professional growth
* Sport activities, parties, team buildings


 If you want to be part of one of the most exciting industries in the world, then apply now and be a key player in our success story!




 We appreciate all applications and interest in Evolution. This is a hybrid - role based in Stockholm, Sweden.
